wift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Onboarding.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Wake.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Profile.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Payments.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/es.lproj/Localizable.strings`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSColors.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSTypography.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSSpacing.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSRadius.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAIButton.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAICard.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAIListRow.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAISkeleton.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yModifiers.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/PaywallFlowUITests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/AppShellSnapshotTests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeContentTests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/WakeTask/WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/FeatureSettingsTests/PaywallViewModelTests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/PaywallSnapshotTests.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/README.md`\n\n## Existing App File Map\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/AppRootView.swift`: top-level route + onboarding modal presentation + theme application.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LaunchRouter.swift`: auth/onboarding gate and first-run routing policy.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/MainTabView.swift`: tab IA (`Home`/`Runs`/`Profile`), paywall/settings sheet entry points, root tab IDs.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeView.swift`: current home layout (hero, quick actions, featured cards, recent runs list).\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeViewModel.swift`: home loading/error/quick-action orchestration.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeContent.swift`: static quick-action and feature-card copy defaults.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift`: list-based wake task list, create/edit sheet, active run controls, reliability rows, existing wake Appium IDs.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeFlowViewModel.swift`: alarm/run lifecycle and state machine used by list/active/completion/history behavior.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingContainerView.swift`: onboarding flow container, skip/next/get-started controls.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPageView.swift`: onboarding page visual treatment and motion behavior.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPage.swift`: onboarding content model/default pages.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/ProfileView.swift`: profile screen composition, settings/paywall launch paths, destructive action alerts.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileSubscriptionSection.swift`: subscription status + restore purchases action.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileQuickActionsSection.swift`: settings/help/legal rows.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileAccountInfoSection.swift`: account metadata rows.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Sources/FeatureSettings/Views/PaywallView.swift`: paywall UI, plan selection, subscribe/restore actions, paywall Appium IDs.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Sources/FeatureSettings/ViewModels/PaywallViewModel.swift`: paywall loading/purchase/restore behavior.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Sources/FeatureSettings/Views/Settings/SettingsSubscriptionSection.swift`: secondary subscription entry point and restore action.\n- `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Onboarding.swift`: onboarding localization accessors.\n- `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Wake.swift`: wake flow/list/reliability/a11y localization accessors.\n- `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Profile.swift`: profile localization accessors.\n- `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Payments.swift`: paywall/subscription localization accessors.\n- `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings`: English string values.\n- `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/es.lproj/Localizable.strings`: Spanish string values.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSColors.swift`: app-level color tokens.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSTypography.swift`: typography tokens and semantic text styles.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSSpacing.swift`: spacing tokens.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSRadius.swift`: corner-radius tokens.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAIButton.swift`: reusable primary/secondary button styling.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAICard.swift`: card container pattern.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAIListRow.swift`: reusable settings/list row pattern.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAISkeleton.swift`: loading placeholder primitives.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yModifiers.swift`: shared accessibility helpers.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests.swift`: smoke launch/tab presence tests.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift`: high-value wake journey automation + telemetry IDs.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/PaywallFlowUITests.swift`: paywall discovery/actions regression tests.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift`: onboarding/auth landing and skip behavior coverage.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/AppShellSnapshotTests.swift`: tab metadata and app-shell smoke checks.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift`: home loading/error behavior validation.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeContentTests.swift`: home content defaults contract tests.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/WakeTask/WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`: wake-state transition correctness tests.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/FeatureSettingsTests/PaywallViewModelTests.swift`: paywall VM unit-level behavior checks.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/PaywallSnapshotTests.swift`: paywall UI snapshot contract.\n- `scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`: CI entrypoint that runs exploratory wake UI test and writes report.\n- `README.md`: current app IA/value framing baseline.\n\n## Screen Spec To File Mapping\n- `onboarding`\n  - SwiftUI: `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingContainerView.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPageView.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPage.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LaunchRouter.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSColors.swift`, `DSTypography.swift`, `DSSpacing.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`.\n  - Localization: `Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/L10n+Onboarding.swift`, `.../Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings`, `.../Resources/es.lproj/Localizable.strings`.\n  - Tests: `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/OnboardingPageTests.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (skip onboarding compatibility).\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `Skip onboarding` semantic discoverability; add explicit IDs for step container, step progress, continue, back, skip, strictness info disclosure.\n- `home`\n  - SwiftUI: `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/HomeView.swift`, `HomeViewModel.swift`, `HomeContent.swift`, `MainTabView.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `DSColors.swift`, `DSTypography.swift`, `SAICard.swift`, `SAIButton.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Common.swift`, `L10n+Wake.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift`, `HomeContentTests.swift`, `AppShellSnapshotTests.swift`, `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests.swift`.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `homeTabRoot`; add `homeNextCommitmentCard`, `homePrimaryActionButton`, `homeViewAllTasksButton`, `homeHistoryPreviewButton`, `homeSyncErrorBanner`, `homeEmptyCreateWakeButton`.\n- `primary_list`\n  - SwiftUI: `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift` (alarms/reliability sections and row actions), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIListRow.swift`, `SAITag.swift`, `DSSectionHeader.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`, `DSColors.swift`.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`, `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (row selectors and resume actions), new UI tests for grouped readiness sections.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve prefix-based IDs `wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeStartRunButton-*`, `wakeEditAlarmButton-*`; add section IDs for `Tonight/Later/Paused` headers and filter/sort controls.\n- `create_edit`\n  - SwiftUI: `WakeDashboardView.swift` (`createAlarmSheet`), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift` (`createAlarm`, `updateAlarm`), potential extracted view `WakeTaskEditorView.swift` (new).\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIButton.swift`, `SAICard.swift`, `SAISkeleton.swift`, spacing/type tokens.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift` + string resources for linear-step labels and inline validation.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift` (create/update semantics), `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (field+save path), new UI test for validation error persistence.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeAlarmNameField`, `wakeAlarmTimePicker`, `wakeStrictnessPicker`, `wakeFirstTaskField`, `wakeAlarmSaveButton`, `wakeAlarmCancelButton`; add step-indicator and advanced-options IDs.\n- `active_task`\n  - SwiftUI: `WakeDashboardView.swift` (`activeRunSection`), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift` (`triggerAlarm`, `completeMission`, `dismissAlarm`, `completeWakeCheck`, `evaluateEscalationIfNeeded`).\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIButton.swift`, `SAICard.swift`, status/chip components, motion token usage.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift`, `L10n+A11y.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`, `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift` (mission completion + wake check + first task progression), add reduced-motion and state-banner ordering UI tests.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeRunStateText`, `wakeMissionButton-*`, `wakeDismissAlarmButton`, `wakeCompleteWakeCheckButton`, `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton`; add `wakeFallbackExtraMinuteButton` and `wakeStateBanner` if fallback pattern is introduced.\n- `completion`\n  - SwiftUI: currently within `WakeDashboardView.swift` active-run lifecycle and post-completion list state; likely extract `WakeCompletionView.swift` (new) while preserving `WakeFlowViewModel` completion state.\n  - Assets/tokens: card, success/recovery status components, typography tokens for summary.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift`, `L10n+Common.swift`, strings files for completion outcome copy and next-best action.\n  - Tests: extend `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift` completion assertions; add dedicated UI test for completion panel and recovery CTA in missed/partial outcomes.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton` path; add `wakeCompletionSummary`, `wakeCompletionPrimaryNextAction`, `wakeCompletionRecoveryAction`, `wakeCompletionGoHomeAction`.\n- `history_streaks`\n  - SwiftUI: `WakeDashboardView.swift` (`reliabilitySection`), `WakeFlowViewModel.swift` (`recentRuns`, consistency calculation), potential extracted `WakeHistoryStreaksView.swift` (new).\n  - Assets/tokens: status chips/tags, section headers, chart/summary card components.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Wake.swift` + new reason-coded labels in strings files.\n  - Tests: `WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift` for reason-coded outcomes and trend calculations; new UI tests for time-range filters and visible repair CTA.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `wakeReliabilityRow-*`, `wakeReliabilityEscalatedBadge`, `wakeReliabilityEmptyText`; add `wakeHistoryTrendSummary`, `wakeHistoryTimeRangeControl`, `wakeHistoryRepairAction`.\n- `profile_settings`\n  - SwiftUI: `ProfileView.swift`, `ProfileAccountInfoSection.swift`, `ProfileQuickActionsSection.swift`, `ProfileSubscriptionSection.swift`, `SettingsSubscriptionSection.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: `SAIListRow.swift`, `DSSectionHeader.swift`, card/list surface tokens.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Profile.swift`, `L10n+Settings.swift`, `L10n+Payments.swift`, strings files.\n  - Tests: `ProfileViewModelTests.swift`, `PaywallFlowUITests.swift` (profile entry paths), add UI tests for section ordering (`Mission Controls`, `Preferences`, `Account/Billing`, `Help/Legal`).\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `profileTabRoot`, `restorePurchasesButton`, `settingsRestorePurchasesButton`; add IDs for mission controls rows, subscription manage action, legal/help rows, destructive confirmations.\n- `paywall_subscription`\n  - SwiftUI: `Packages/FeatureSettings/.../PaywallView.swift`, `PaywallViewModel.swift`, `SettingsSubscriptionSection.swift`, `ProfileSubscriptionSection.swift`, paywall sheet presentation in `MainTabView.swift`.\n  - Assets/tokens: button, card, typography, status color tokens.\n  - Localization: `L10n+Payments.swift`, strings files for premium value framing and restore/purchase copy.\n  - Tests: `PaywallViewModelTests.swift`, `PaywallSnapshotTests.swift`, `PaywallFlowUITests.swift`.\n  - Appium IDs: preserve `paywallSubscribeButton`, `paywallRestoreButton`, `paywallErrorBanner`, `restorePurchasesButton`; add `paywallPrimaryValueHeader`, `paywallPlanOption-*`, `paywallCloseButton`, `paywallMaybeLaterButton`.\n\n## Expected SwiftUI Components\n- Design token wrappers: `WakeColorTokens`, `WakeTypographyTokens`, `WakeSpacingTokens` adapters over `DSColors`, `DSTypography`, `DSSpacing`.\n- Theme colors: commitment/status palette mapping to `color.action.*` and `color.state.*` semantics.\n- Typography helpers: Dynamic Type-safe title/subtitle/status helpers with tabular numerals for times/streaks.\n- Cards: `NextCommitmentCard`, `WakeTaskCard`, `OutcomeSummaryCard`, `ReliabilityTrendCard`.\n- Rows: `WakeTaskRow`, `HistoryOutcomeRow`, `SettingsActionRow`.\n- Progress/status components: `WakeStepProgress`, `WakeStateBanner`, `ReadinessChip`, `ReliabilityStatusChip`.\n- Primary actions: `WakePrimaryCTA` with one-dominant-action rules for active/completion screens.\n- Empty/error/loading states: reusable `WakeEmptyState`, `WakeInlineErrorBanner`, `WakeScreenSkeleton` wrappers around `SAISkeleton`.\n- Accessibility wrappers: focus-order modifiers, VoiceOver summary builders, reduced-motion alternatives, minimum-hit-target wrappers.\n\n## Tests To Update\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/AppShellSnapshotTests.swift`: assert updated tab metadata and IA labels remain stable.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeViewModelTests.swift`: prove home empty/loading/error/loaded commitment states remain deterministic.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/HomeContentTests.swift`: prove default home quick actions and wake-specific labels align with calm-accountability copy.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/WakeTask/WakeFlowViewModelTests.swift`: prove active->dismissed->verified->completed transitions and reason-code outcomes remain correct.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/OnboardingPageTests.swift`: prove onboarding step model and copy/order constraints.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/FeatureSettingsTests/PaywallViewModelTests.swift`: prove offerings load, purchase/restore error paths, and subscription state transitions.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings/Tests/PaywallSnapshotTests.swift`: prove paywall visual hierarchy and CTA ordering in light/dark and Dynamic Type.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests.swift`: prove launch path still exposes required tabs and root surfaces.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift`: prove critical end-to-end wake flow still automation-reachable with updated identifiers.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/PaywallFlowUITests.swift`: prove paywall open/close/select/subscribe/restore behavior and profile entry paths.\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/AuthFlowUITests.swift`: prove onboarding skip and auth transitions still function with revised onboarding controls.\n- `scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`: prove telemetry report still captures visited screens and tapped IDs after identifier updates.\n- Add screenshot-manifest validation test (new, repo-local): prove required before/after screenshot IDs and variants exist in manifest JSON.\n\n## Screenshot States To Capture\n- Current baseline artifact status: real baseline capture is currently blocked in this worker because `xcrun` is unavailable; baseline manifest should be captured in hosted iOS validation environment.\n- Required before/after states per screen (`onboarding`, `home`, `primary_list`, `create_edit`, `active_task`, `completion`, `history_streaks`, `profile_settings`, `paywall_subscription`):\n  - `before/default`\n  - `after/default`\n  - `empty`\n  - `loading`\n  - `error`\n  - `success` (where applicable)\n  - `active_task` live state and fallback state\n  - `completion` success and missed/partial recovery state\n  - `paywall/subscription` free-state paywall, subscribed state, restore error state\n  - Dynamic Type (`AX2` or equivalent large size)\n  - dark mode variant\n- Additional named states from `screen-spec.json` to capture explicitly:\n  - `onboarding`: defaults populated, save/validation error, skip-visible.\n  - `home`: no-commitment empty, sync-failure banner with last-known summary.\n  - `primary_list`: grouped readiness sections (`Tonight`, `Later`, `Paused`) and section-level retry.\n  - `create_edit`: step progress visible, inline field validation, advanced options collapsed/expanded.\n  - `active_task`: single dominant CTA, explicit state banner, safe fallback action.\n  - `completion`: next-best primary action and secondary history/repair options.\n  - `history_streaks`: trend summary with reason-coded outcomes and repair CTA.\n  - `profile_settings`: section ordering mission-first then preferences then account/billing then help/legal.\n  - `paywall_subscription`: contextual premium value framing with non-blocking dismissal.\n\n## Appium Identifier Changes\n- Preserve existing identifiers:\n  - `homeTabRoot`, `wakeTabRoot`, `profileTabRoot`.\n  - Wake flow IDs: `wakeAddAlarmButton`, `wakeAlarmNameField`, `wakeAlarmTimePicker`, `wakeStrictnessPicker`, `wakeFirstTaskField`, `wakeAlarmSaveButton`, `wakeAlarmCancelButton`, `wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeStartRunButton-*`, `wakeEditAlarmButton-*`, `wakeMissionButton-*`, `wakeDismissAlarmButton`, `wakeCompleteWakeCheckButton`, `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton`, `wakeRunStateText`, `wakeReliabilityRow-*`, `wakeReliabilityEscalatedBadge`, `wakeReliabilityEmptyText`.\n  - Paywall/subscription IDs: `paywallSubscribeButton`, `paywallRestoreButton`, `paywallErrorBanner`, `restorePurchasesButton`, `settingsRestorePurchasesButton`.\n- Add identifiers:\n  - Onboarding: `onboardingStepProgress`, `onboardingContinueButton`, `onboardingBackButton`, `onboardingSkipButton`, `onboardingStrictnessInfoButton`.\n  - Home: `homeNextCommitmentCard`, `homePrimaryActionButton`, `homeViewAllTasksButton`, `homeHistoryPreviewButton`, `homeEmptyCreateWakeButton`, `homeSyncErrorBanner`.\n  - List/history/completion/profile: `wakeReadinessTonightSection`, `wakeReadinessLaterSection`, `wakeReadinessPausedSection`, `wakeHistoryTrendSummary`, `wakeHistoryRepairAction`, `wakeCompletionPrimaryNextAction`, `wakeCompletionRecoveryAction`, `profileMissionControlsSection`, `profilePreferencesSection`, `profileAccountBillingSection`, `profileHelpLegalSection`.\n  - Paywall: `paywallPlanOption-*`, `paywallMaybeLaterButton`, `paywallCloseButton`.\n- Rename strategy:\n  - Keep existing IDs as aliases for one release where feasible, then migrate tests to new IDs and remove aliases after CI/Appium parity passes.\n  - Avoid renaming dynamic prefix IDs (`wakeAlarmCell-*`, `wakeMissionButton-*`) to keep exploratory selectors stable.\n- Automation discoverability guarantees:\n  - Buttons/tabs: explicit stable IDs + visible labels.\n  - Cells/rows: prefix-based IDs for generated items.\n  - Navigation controls: dedicated IDs for back/close/sheet dismiss.\n  - Paywall actions: explicit subscribe/restore/close/maybe-later IDs.\n  - Task actions: one ID per dominant and fallback action in active/completion states.\n\n## Phase Breakdown\n- `visual-system`\n  - Scope: map `screen-spec` semantics to DS tokens/components, define calm-accountability component set, and lock accessibility defaults.\n  - Deliverables: token mapping doc + reusable components + previews for light/dark/Dynamic Type.\n  - Exit tests: DesignSystem token/component tests + snapshot updates pass.\n- `screen-flows`\n  - Scope: apply component system to each target screen in app-shell and paywall paths without changing auth/payments/network/storage architecture.\n  - Deliverables: onboarding/home/list/create-edit/active/completion/history/profile/paywall UI updates with preserved behavior contracts.\n  - Exit tests: updated unit/UI/paywall tests pass; Appium exploratory test passes with migrated IDs.\n- `ux-quality-review`\n  - Scope: hosted iOS screenshot capture, contrast/VoiceOver/Dynamic Type/reduced-motion checks, and regression triage.\n  - Deliverables: before/after screenshot manifest, UX validation notes, and postmortem learning capture artifact.\n  - Exit tests: screenshot-manifest gate + accessibility checklist + acceptance criteria signoff.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- All 9 screen IDs from `screen-spec.json` are implemented and mapped to production SwiftUI surfaces.\n- One-primary-action rule is met on wake-critical surfaces (`active_task`, `completion`) with visible fallback path.\n- Required empty/loading/error/success states are present and stable in layout.\n- Localization keys exist for new user-facing copy in at least `en` and `es` resources.\n- Existing protected systems remain unchanged in behavior: auth, payments, entitlement, networking, storage, localization infrastructure, bundle/release config.\n- UITest/Appium selectors remain discoverable and CI-stable after identifier migration.\n- Hosted iOS validation produces required before/after screenshot states, including Dynamic Type and dark mode.\n- No competitor asset/copy/layout cloning in final UI.\n\n## Explicit Non-Goals\n- No auth rebuild.\n- No payment rebuild.\n- No networking/storage rewrite.\n- No bundle ID changes.\n- No copied competitor assets.\n- No replacement of LaunchRouter auth/onboarding decision model.\n- No changes to RevenueCat wiring or entitlement logic.\n- No schema/storage migration for this phase unless approved by later ADR.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md\"","aggregated_output":"# UX Screen Spec\n## Winning Direction Summary\n- Winning direction: `calm_accountability_direction`.\n- Product emotion: grounded first impression, low-friction wake execution, steady recovery after misses.\n- Core posture: one primary action per screen in wake-critical moments; progressive disclosure for complexity.\n- Monetization stance: free core wake loop remains intact; premium adds reliability tools and deeper insights only.\n- No-clone boundary: adapt interaction principles only; do not replicate external visual/copy/motion signatures.\n\n## Global Visual System\n- Visual principles: medium-compact density on home/list, low density on active/completion, neutral surfaces, strong text contrast.\n- Accent usage: calm blue-green accent reserved for commitment actions and positive confirmations.\n- State signaling: hierarchy, text, and iconography first; color never the sole signal.\n- Semantic tokens:\n  - `color.bg.primary`, `color.bg.secondary`, `color.surface.card`\n  - `color.text.primary`, `color.text.secondary`, `color.text.muted`\n  - `color.action.primary`, `color.action.primaryPressed`, `color.action.secondary`\n  - `color.state.success`, `color.state.warning`, `color.state.destructive`, `color.state.disabled`\n  - `color.state.focusRing`, `color.state.highContrastBorder`\n- Typography: Dynamic Type semantic styles only, multiline-safe labels, tabular numerals for timers/streak counts.\n- Motion: restrained transitions; reduced-motion path uses crossfades/static swaps; no looping urgency animations.\n\n## Global Accessibility Requirements\n- VoiceOver: explicit labels and verbs for every status chip, state banner, and primary CTA.\n- Focus order: top-down, action-first in wake-critical screens, with fallback action immediately after primary CTA.\n- Dynamic Type: no fixed-size text on critical surfaces; multiline expansion with stable card/container growth.\n- Contrast: WCAG-safe text/background and chip/border contrast in light, dark, and high-contrast modes.\n- Reduced motion: every animated transition has non-motion equivalent with equal semantic clarity.\n- Haptic alternatives: all success/warning/failure signals also shown via visible text/icon state.\n- Target sizes: interactive targets at least 44x44pt.\n- One-handed reach: primary wake CTA within lower-thumb zone on large devices.\n\n## Screens\n### onboarding\n- Purpose: establish wake intent, default timing, and optional strictness with reversible setup.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Step progress and intent headline\n  - Current step controls (intent, schedule, strictness)\n  - Primary CTA (`Continue`/`Finish setup`)\n  - Secondary controls (`Skip for now`, `Back`)\n- Primary action: advance setup with explicit confirmation of current choice.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Skip for now` in top-right or bottom secondary button\n  - `Back` in nav bar\n  - `Learn more` inline disclosure for strictness terms\n- Empty state: default recommendation cards (e.g., “Weekday wake at 7:00 AM”) with editable values.\n- Loading state: skeleton for step card and CTA; reserved space for helper text to prevent layout jump.\n- Error state: inline validation and retry message (e.g., schedule save failed) with preserved form values.\n- Copy direction: calm, factual, supportive (“Set your first wake commitment”); avoid guilt or pressure phrases; keep labels short for localization expansion.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces step count and current selection.\n  - Focus order: title -> step controls -> primary CTA -> secondary actions.\n  - Dynamic Type keeps step body multiline without truncating CTA labels.\n  - Reduced motion removes step-slide animation.\n  - One-handed safe: primary CTA anchored near bottom.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Primary CTA visible without scrolling.\n  - Step title and CTA not truncated at common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Skip path visible and clearly secondary.\n  - Light/dark screenshots preserve readable hierarchy and non-color state cues.\n  - Loading and error variants keep card and CTA positions stable.\n\n### home\n- Purpose: show the next wake commitment and provide immediate path to prepare or start.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - `Next Wake Commitment` module\n  - Commitment status line and time context\n  - Primary CTA (`Review wake` or `Start when due`)\n  - Secondary modules (history preview, profile shortcut)\n- Primary action: open the next wake commitment flow.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `View all tasks` link below commitment card\n  - `History` preview tap target\n  - Profile/settings icon in top-right\n- Empty state: “No wake commitments yet” with `Create your first wake` CTA.\n- Loading state: skeleton commitment card with fixed-height placeholder for status text and CTA.\n- Error state: sync/load failure banner with `Retry` and last-known commitment snapshot.\n- Copy direction: operational clarity (“Next wake: Tomorrow 7:00 AM”); avoid vague motivation-only copy; localizable date/time formats.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver reads commitment title, due time, and state in one coherent phrase.\n  - Focus order prioritizes commitment card and primary CTA before analytics tiles.\n  - Dynamic Type wraps status line and keeps CTA fully readable.\n  - Contrast-safe status chips with text labels/icons.\n  - One-handed reach keeps primary card action in thumb zone.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Next commitment card is first visible module.\n  - Primary CTA visible without scroll.\n  - Status is understandable without relying on color alone.\n  - No critical text truncation on common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Light/dark mode screenshots preserve legibility and hierarchy.\n\n### primary_list\n- Purpose: manage all wake tasks grouped by readiness for quick scanning and resume.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Readiness sections (`Tonight`, `Later`, `Paused`)\n  - Task rows with time, status chip, and quick action\n  - Primary list CTA (`Create wake task`)\n  - Filters/sort as secondary controls\n- Primary action: resume or open the most relevant task in readiness groups.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Pause/Resume` swipe or row action\n  - `Edit` from row overflow\n  - `Filter` control in header\n- Empty state: sectioned guidance with `Create wake task` CTA and short explanation of readiness groups.\n- Loading state: section headers and row skeletons with stable row height.\n- Error state: inline section error with retry; unaffected sections remain visible.\n- Copy direction: plain labels (“Paused”, “Tonight”), no novelty jargon; avoid punitive miss language; ensure short translatable chips.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces section + task + state + available action.\n  - Focus order follows section header then rows.\n  - Dynamic Type allows multiline task titles and wraps metadata.\n  - 44x44pt minimum for row actions and overflow menu.\n  - Non-haptic cues for pause/resume confirmation.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Readiness sections visibly distinct by headings, not color only.\n  - At least one row shows clear status chip text/icon.\n  - Primary create CTA visible without scroll in empty state.\n  - Dynamic Type does not clip row action labels.\n  - Loading/error states preserve row geometry.\n\n### create/edit\n- Purpose: author or revise a wake task through linear, low-cognitive configuration.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Step sequence (`Intent -> Timing -> Safeguards -> Review`)\n  - Current step fields\n  - Primary CTA (`Continue`/`Save wake task`)\n  - Secondary actions (`Cancel`, `Advanced options`)\n- Primary action: complete current step and move forward to final save.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Advanced options` disclosure below core fields\n  - `Cancel` in nav bar\n  - `Back` to previous step\n- Empty state: prefilled starter values with concise explanations and defaults.\n- Loading state: form section skeletons with preserved field spacing and fixed footer CTA area.\n- Error state: inline field errors and top summary for save/sync failure with retry.\n- Copy direction: explicit and instructional (“Choose your wake window”); avoid legalistic or alarmist phrasing; localize numeric/time units cleanly.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver reads field label, value, and validation state.\n  - Focus order is step header -> fields -> primary CTA -> secondary actions.\n  - Dynamic Type allows multiline helper text and non-overlapping controls.\n  - Reduced motion disables animated step transitions.\n  - One-handed reach keeps primary CTA in bottom action bar.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Current step and progress context clearly visible.\n  - Primary CTA visible without scrolling on each step.\n  - Error screenshot shows preserved input and clear correction guidance.\n  - No truncation of key field labels at common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Layout stability between loading and filled states.\n\n### active_task\n- Purpose: execute a live wake commitment with one dominant action and explicit state.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Current-state banner (e.g., `Wake Check In Progress`)\n  - Dominant primary CTA (`I'm awake` or equivalent state action)\n  - Fallback action (clearly labeled, lower emphasis)\n  - Minimal contextual details/timer\n- Primary action: confirm wake completion step for current state.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `Need extra minute` fallback button below primary CTA\n  - `View details` collapsed disclosure\n- Empty state: not applicable; if no active task, redirect to home with explanatory message.\n- Loading state: state banner and disabled CTA placeholders while status sync resolves.\n- Error state: explicit sync/permission failure banner with retry and safe fallback path.\n- Copy direction: short imperative clarity (“Confirm you’re awake”); avoid shaming, urgency theatrics, or dense text; localization-safe verbs.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces current state before actionable controls.\n  - Focus order: state banner -> primary CTA -> fallback -> details.\n  - High contrast for primary action and state text in both themes.\n  - Reduced motion removes transition flourishes; state updates remain textual.\n  - Primary CTA 44x44pt minimum and thumb reachable.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Exactly one visually dominant primary action.\n  - Fallback action is visible and clearly secondary.\n  - State is understandable without motion or color-only cues.\n  - Dark/light screenshots both show clear CTA contrast.\n  - Loading/error variants keep CTA and banner positions stable.\n\n### completion\n- Purpose: confirm outcome, reinforce continuity, and route to one next-best action.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Completion confirmation message\n  - Outcome summary (time/status)\n  - Primary next action (`Set next wake` or `Quick reflection`)\n  - Secondary repair/help actions\n- Primary action: choose the recommended next step to sustain continuity.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - `View history` link\n  - `Repair missed wake` when relevant\n  - Dismiss/back to home\n- Empty state: if opened without prior task, show neutral guidance and `Go to home` CTA.\n- Loading state: confirmation card skeleton with reserved next-action button space.\n- Error state: failure saving completion/notes shows retry with preserved summary.\n- Copy direction: respectful, factual (“Wake completed at 7:02 AM”); avoid celebratory pressure or guilt; keep concise localizable phrasing.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces completion state and next action recommendation.\n  - Focus order prioritizes next action before tertiary links.\n  - Dynamic Type keeps summary and CTA multiline-safe.\n  - Non-color indicators for success/recovery states.\n  - Haptic confirmation always paired with text/icon confirmation.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Confirmation state is immediately visible above fold.\n  - Primary next action visible without scroll.\n  - Recovery path present for missed/partial outcomes without punitive copy.\n  - No key truncation in common Dynamic Type sizes.\n  - Visual structure stable across loading/error states.\n\n### history/streaks\n- Purpose: show reliability trend, explain outcome reasons, and enable repair planning.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Reliability summary/trend module\n  - Reason-coded entries (`completed`, `missed`, `recovered`)\n  - Primary CTA (`Plan repair` when needed or `Set next wake`)\n  - Secondary filters/time-range controls\n- Primary action: initiate repair planning or next wake setup from current reliability context.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - Time-range segmented control\n  - Entry detail drill-in\n  - Export/share if available as tertiary\n- Empty state: no history yet message with `Complete your first wake` guidance.\n- Loading state: chart/list skeletons with fixed axes/header footprint to avoid jump.\n- Error state: partial data notice with retry; stale cached entries remain visible.\n- Copy direction: explanatory accountability (“Missed: alarm silenced early”); avoid blame language; keep reason labels short and translatable.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver reads trend direction and each entry reason as text.\n  - Focus order: summary -> primary CTA -> entries -> filters.\n  - Dynamic Type supports multiline reason text and chip expansion.\n  - Charts/rings must have text equivalents.\n  - One-handed reach for primary repair CTA.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Reason-coded outcomes visible as text, not color alone.\n  - Primary action visible without scroll in relevant state.\n  - Trend remains legible in light/dark modes.\n  - Dynamic Type does not clip reason labels.\n  - Loading/error maintain stable chart/list containers.\n\n### profile/settings\n- Purpose: separate mission controls from preferences, billing, and legal/support.\n- Hierarchy:\n  - Mission Controls section\n  - Preferences section\n  - Account/Billing section\n  - Help/Legal section\n- Primary action: access mission-critical settings quickly and safely.\n- Secondary actions:\n  - Manage subscription within Account/Billing\n  - Help/contact actions in Help/Legal\n  - Sign out/delete account as guarded destructive flows\n- Empty state: account-not-synced state with sign-in/retry prompt and local settings access.\n- Loading state: section skeleton rows with fixed grouping spacing.\n- Error state: account/billing fetch error inline with retry; mission settings remain accessible.\n- Copy direction: plain and specific section labels; avoid mixing legal/account terms with wake execution labels; localization-safe row titles.\n- Accessibility requirements:\n  - VoiceOver announces section boundaries and row purpose.\n  - Focus order follows section order, mission-first.\n  - Dynamic Type allows multiline row labels and subtitles.\n  - Destructive actions include explicit text/icon confirmation.\n  - Touch targets for rows and toggles meet minimum size.\n- Screenshot acceptance criteria:\n  - Section separation is visually obvious.\n  - Mission Controls appears above Account/Billing and Help/Legal.\n  - No truncation of section headers or row labels at common Dynamic Type sizes.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/evidence/visual-system.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Visual System Evidence\n## Files changed\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/WakeVisualTokens.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/WakeVisualComponents.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/WakeAccessibility.swift`\n- `apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Tests/DesignSystemTests/WakeVisualSystemTests.swift`\n\n## Commands run\n- `rg --files .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio apps/waketask-ios | sed -n '1,240p'`\n- `sed -n '1,240p' .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/implementation-plan.md`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.md`\n- `cat .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json`\n- `rg --files apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem | sed -n '1,260p'`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSColors.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/DSTypography.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAIButton.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAICard.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAIListRow.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Components/SAISkeleton.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yModifiers.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Package.swift`\n- `rg --files apps/waketask-ios/Packages/DesignSystem/Tests | sed -n '1,240p'`\n- `swift test` (failed in worker: `swift: command not found`)\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- Design tokens and theme colors: Added app-specific semantic layer in `WakeColorTokens` for light/dark-consumable semantics including disabled, destructive, success, warning, premium, and active-task tones; mapped over existing `DSColors` where available.\n- Reusable app-specific components: Added dedicated `Wake` component set (`WakeCard`, `WakeRow`, `WakeStatusChip`, `WakeProgressStatus`, primary/secondary action buttons, empty/loading/error/premium/completion states) instead of one-off styling.\n- Dynamic Type typography wrappers: Added `WakeTypography` semantic wrappers using Dynamic Type text styles and a monospaced-digit option for timers/streak-style values.\n- Cards/rows/progress-status direction fit: Added calm-accountability surface/row/status abstractions reflecting single-primary-action, explicit state labeling, and stable card geometry.\n- VoiceOver support: Added component-level labels/traits and helpers (`wakeStateAccessibility`, focus priority utilities, min target helper) for tappable/stateful surfaces.\n- Test/preview coverage: Added component previews for light/dark and accessibility Dynamic Type; added `WakeVisualSystemTests` for token and component invariants including semantic state mappings.\n- Existing behavior preserved: No auth/payment/entitlement/networking/storage/navigation behavior files were modified.\n- Independent verification status: Left pending per requirement.\n\n## Component inventory\n- Tokens: `WakeColorTokens`, `WakeStateTone`, `WakeTypography`, `WakeSpacing`\n- Cards and layout: `WakeCard`\n- Rows: `WakeRow`\n- Status/progress: `WakeStatusChip`, `WakeProgressStatus`\n- Actions: `WakePrimaryActionButton`, `WakeSecondaryActionButton`\n- Empty/loading/error: `WakeEmptyStateView`, `WakeLoadingStateView`, `WakeErrorStateView`\n- Premium callout: `WakePremiumCallout`\n- Completion feedback: `WakeCompletionFeedback`\n- Accessibility helpers: `WakeFocusOrder`, `wakeMinimumTapTarget()`, `wakeFocusPriority(_:)`, `wakeStateAccessibility(label:hint:)`, `wakeMotionAwareAnimation(_:)`\n\n## Accessibility notes\n- 44pt minimum target intent enforced in wake action components and helper modifiers.\n- Stateful chips and banners include text + icon semantics (not color only).\n- Focus-order utilities support action-first sequencing for wake-critical states.\n- Motion-aware helper provides reduce-motion-safe animation fallback behavior.\n- Typography wrappers rely on Dynamic Type semantic fonts and multiline-safe text configuration in key components.\n\n## Screenshot states prepared\n- Previews added for default mixed-state component stack.\n- Previews added for loading state.\n- Previews added for empty state.\n- Previews added for error state.\n- Previews added for premium callout state.\n- Previews added for completion feedback state.\n- Previews added for active-task progress/status state.\n- Previews added for dark mode variant.\n- Previews added for Dynamic Type accessibility size (`.accessibility2`) variant.\n\n## Risks\n- `swift` toolchain is unavailable in this worker, so tests/previews were validated statically but not executed here.\n- New components are introduced and previewed in DesignSystem but not yet wired through all app screen call-sites in this phase.\n- High-contrast runtime verification depends on host iOS simulator/device checks in verifier stage.\n\n## Verifier notes\n- Pending independent verifier.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' .workflow/iphone-app-ux-studio/design/screen-spec.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"winning_direction\": \"calm_accountability_direction\",\n  \"global_visual_system\": {\n    \"target_emotion\": \"Grounded first impression, focused wake execution without panic, and steady recovery-oriented accountability.\",\n    \"tokens\": [\n      \"color.bg.primary\",\n      \"color.bg.secondary\",\n      \"color.surface.card\",\n      \"color.text.primary\",\n      \"color.text.secondary\",\n      \"color.text.muted\",\n      \"color.action.primary\",\n      \"color.action.primaryPressed\",\n      \"color.action.secondary\",\n      \"color.state.success\",\n      \"color.state.warning\",\n      \"color.state.destructive\",\n      \"color.state.disabled\",\n      \"color.state.focusRing\",\n      \"color.state.highContrastBorder\"\n    ],\n    \"typography\": \"Use Dynamic Type semantic styles with multiline-safe hierarchy, tabular numerals for timers and streak values, and no fixed-size text on wake-critical surfaces.\",\n    \"motion\": \"Use restrained state transitions, no looping urgency motion, and reduced-motion equivalents via crossfade or static swaps with identical semantic clarity.\"\n  },\n  \"screens\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"onboarding\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Capture intent, default schedule, and optional strictness through a reversible three-step setup.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Step progress and intent headline\",\n        \"Current step controls\",\n        \"Primary continuation action\",\n        \"Skip and back controls\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Advance setup with Continue/Finish setup after each explicit selection.\",\n      \"secondary_actions\": [\n        \"Skip for now in a clearly visible secondary position\",\n        \"Back navigation in the top bar\",\n        \"Optional learn-more disclosure for strictness\"\n      ],\n      \"states\": {\n        \"empty\": \"Show editable recommended defaults so users can complete setup quickly.\",\n        \"loading\": \"Show step card skeleton and stable CTA placement while defaults load.\",\n        \"error\": \"Show inline save/validation errors with retry while preserving entered values.\"\n      },\n      \"copy_direction\": \"Calm and factual tone with short labels; avoid guilt, pressure, and coercive wording; preserve localization headroom for expanded strings.\",\n      \"accessibility_requirements\": [\n        \"VoiceOver announces step count, current choice, and CTA outcome.\",\n        \"Focus order is title to controls to primary CTA to secondary actions.\",\n        \"Dynamic Type supports multiline fields and untruncated CTA labels.\",\n        \"Reduced motion removes step-slide animations.\",\n        \"Primary CTA remains reachable in lower-thumb zone and meets 44x44pt target size.\"\n      ],\n      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n        \"Primary CTA is visible without scrolling.\",\n        \"Step title and CTA labels are readable at common Dynamic Type sizes.\",\n        \"Skip path is visible and clearly secondary.\",\n        \"Light and dark mode both preserve contrast and hierarchy.\",\n        \"Loading and error states keep card and button positions stable.\",\n        \"Visual composition does not clone any named competitor reference.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"home\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Orient users to the next wake commitment and provide immediate preparation or start action.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Next Wake Commitment module\",\n        \"Commitment status and due-time context\",\n        \"Primary commitment action\",\n        \"Secondary history and profile shortcuts\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Open the next wake commitment flow from the dominant home module.\",\n      \"secondary_actions\": [\n        \"View all tasks link beneath commitment module\",\n        \"History preview navigation\",\n        \"Profile/settings access\"\n      ],\n      \"states\": {\n        \"empty\": \"Show no-commitment message with Create your first wake action.\",\n        \"loading\": \"Show commitment card skeleton with reserved status and CTA space.\",\n        \"error\": \"Show sync failure banner with Retry while preserving last-known commitment summary.\"\n      },\n      \"copy_direction\": \"Use operational clarity and plain scheduling language; avoid vague hype or pressure; localize date/time formats natively.\",\n      \"accessibility_requirements\": [\n        \"VoiceOver reads commitment title, due time, and status as one coherent summary.\",\n        \"Focus order prioritizes commitment content before analytics tiles.\",\n        \"Dynamic Type allows multiline status text without clipping action labels.\",\n        \"Status chips include text/icon semantics and are not color-only.\",\n        \"Primary action remains one-handed reachable and target-size compliant.\"\n      ],\n      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n        \"Next Wake Commitment is the first visible module.\",\n        \"Primary action is above the fold.\",\n        \"Status meaning is clear without depending on color alone.\",\n        \"No key text truncation at common Dynamic Type sizes.\",\n        \"Dark and light mode screenshots remain readable.\",\n        \"Layout remains stable between loading/error and loaded states.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"primary_list\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Let users scan and manage wake tasks by readiness with quick resume or edit actions.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Readiness sections Tonight, Later, and Paused\",\n        \"Task rows with status chips and quick actions\",\n        \"Primary create action\",\n        \"Secondary filter and sort controls\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Resume or open the most relevant task from readiness-grouped rows.\",\n      \"secondary_actions\": [\n        \"Pause or Resume row actions\",\n        \"Edit from row overflow\",\n        \"Filter and sorting controls\"\n      ],\n      \"states\": {\n        \"empty\": \"Show readiness explanation and create-task CTA.\",\n        \"loading\": \"Show section and row skeletons with stable heights.\",\n        \"error\": \"Show section-level load error with retry while unaffected sections stay visible.\"\n      },\n      \"copy_direction\": \"Prefer plain status terms and concise chips; avoid jargon and punitive miss language; keep labels short for localization.\",\n      \"accessibility_requirements\": [\n        \"VoiceOver announces section, task title, status, and available quick action.\",\n        \"Focus order is section header then rows in reading order.\",\n        \"Dynamic Type supports multiline row titles and metadata.\",\n        \"Row controls meet minimum touch targets and have explicit labels.\",\n        \"Pause/Resume confirmation is never haptic-only.\"\n      ],\n      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n        \"Readiness grouping is visually clear via headings, not color alone.\",\n        \"Status chip text is readable in at least one visible row.\",\n        \"Empty-state create action is visible above fold.\",\n        \"Dynamic Type does not clip row actions or key labels.\",\n        \"Loading and error variants preserve row geometry.\",\n        \"Screen styling does not replicate a competitor list composition.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"create_edit\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Guide users through linear wake-task authoring from intent to review with progressive disclosure.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Step sequence indicator\",\n        \"Current-step form fields\",\n        \"Primary continue or save action\",\n        \"Secondary back, cancel, and advanced options\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Complete the current step and advance to final task save.\",\n      \"secondary_actions\": [\n        \"Advanced options disclosure below core fields\",\n        \"Back navigation\",\n        \"Cancel action in navigation bar\"\n      ],\n      \"states\": {\n        \"empty\": \"Show starter defaults and concise field guidance.\",\n        \"loading\": \"Show form skeletons with fixed footer CTA area.\",\n        \"error\": \"Show inline field errors and save-failure summary with retry.\"\n      },\n      \"copy_direction\": \"Use concise instructional language; avoid alarmist or legalistic phrasing; keep units/time terms localization-friendly.\",\n      \"accessibility_requirements\": [\n        \"VoiceOver reads field label, value, and validation status.\",\n        \"Focus order follows step header to fields to primary action.\",\n        \"Dynamic Type supports multiline helper text and avoids control overlap.\",\n        \"Reduced motion removes step transition animations.\",\n        \"Primary CTA remains in one-handed reach and meets minimum target size.\"\n      ],\n      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n        \"Current step context is clearly visible.\",\n        \"Primary continue/save action is visible without scrolling.\",\n        \"Error state preserves entered data and correction guidance.\",\n        \"No critical field labels truncate at common Dynamic Type sizes.\",\n        \"Loading and loaded layouts keep stable vertical rhythm.\",\n        \"Visual hierarchy avoids clone-like replication of reference flows.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"active_task\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Enable rapid wake execution with one dominant action, explicit state clarity, and a safe fallback.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Current-state banner\",\n        \"Dominant wake confirmation CTA\",\n        \"Fallback action\",\n        \"Minimal supporting context\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Confirm current wake step completion with the single dominant CTA.\",\n      \"secondary_actions\": [\n        \"Need extra minute fallback action\",\n        \"Optional details disclosure\"\n      ],\n      \"states\": {\n        \"empty\": \"If no active wake exists, redirect to home with clear explanatory text.\",\n        \"loading\": \"Show state banner and disabled CTA placeholders while syncing.\",\n        \"error\": \"Show explicit sync or permission failure with retry and safe fallback path.\"\n      },\n      \"copy_direction\": \"Use short direct verbs and immediate context; avoid shame, panic theatrics, and dense explanatory text.\",\n      \"accessibility_requirements\": [\n        \"VoiceOver announces state banner before interactive controls.\",\n        \"Focus order is state to primary CTA to fallback to details.\",\n        \"Primary CTA and state text meet contrast requirements in both themes.\",\n        \"Reduced motion removes transition effects while preserving text state updates.\",\n        \"Primary and fallback controls meet target size and one-handed reach constraints.\"\n      ],\n      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n        \"Exactly one visually dominant primary action is present.\",\n        \"Fallback action is visible and clearly secondary.\",\n        \"State meaning is clear without motion or color-only dependency.\",\n        \"Dark and light mode both show legible CTA and state banner.\",\n        \"Loading and error variants keep button and banner alignment stable.\",\n        \"Screen does not visually clone known alarm-challenge competitors.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"completion\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Confirm wake outcome and direct the user to one next-best continuity action.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Completion confirmation\",\n        \"Outcome summary\",\n        \"Primary next-best action\",\n        \"Secondary history or repair options\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Take the recommended next step such as Set next wake or Quick reflection.\",\n      \"secondary_actions\": [\n        \"View history\",\n        \"Repair path when outcome is missed or partial\",\n        \"Return to home\"\n      ],\n      \"states\": {\n        \"empty\": \"Show neutral fallback and home return action when no completion record exists.\",\n        \"loading\": \"Show confirmation card skeleton with stable next-action slot.\",\n        \"error\": \"Show save failure and retry while preserving completion summary context.\"\n      },\n      \"copy_direction\": \"Keep tone respectful and factual; avoid manipulative celebration pressure or guilt framing; use concise localizable labels.\",\n      \"accessibility_requirements\": [\n        \"VoiceOver announces outcome then recommended next action.\",\n        \"Focus order prioritizes next-best action before tertiary links.\",\n        \"Dynamic Type keeps summary and action labels readable across multiline expansion.\",\n        \"Success/recovery indicators are text/icon reinforced, not color-only.\",\n        \"Haptic feedback always has visible text equivalent.\"\n      ],\n      \"screenshot_acceptance_criteria\": [\n        \"Completion confirmation is immediately visible above fold.\",\n        \"Primary next action is visible without scroll.\",\n        \"Recovery option is present in missed/partial state and non-punitive.\",\n        \"No key text truncation at common Dynamic Type sizes.\",\n        \"Loading and error states preserve card and button placement.\",\n        \"Visual style avoids direct clone of any referenced app.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"history_streaks\",\n      \"purpose\": \"Show reliability trend with reason-coded outcomes and provide quick repair planning.\",\n      \"hierarchy\": [\n        \"Reliability trend summary\",\n        \"Reason-coded outcome entries\",\n        \"Primary repair or next-wake action\",\n        \"Secondary filters and drill-ins\"\n      ],\n      \"primary_action\": \"Start repair planning or set the next wake from current reliability context.\",\n      